== General Principles for RKC

Four of a previously bid major is natural.
However, we use 4S as kickback for hearts when we have agreed hearts
and it when it is not a picture jump.

=== Set trumps first

CAUTION: If itâ€™s possible to set a suit as trump with an unambiguous
below-game forcing-bid, then that route must be taken to ask for
key-cards in that suit.

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1H |  1S   | |
| 2H |  ?    | |
|    |  2NT  | | natural inv.
|    |  3H   | | inv.
|    |  3S   | | forcing, at most a one-loser suit
|    | !4C!  | | splinter [nobr]##(#could be fake#)##
|    |  4H   | | to play
|    |  4S   | | to play
|    | !4NT! | | #natural inv.#
           [nobr]#(forcing-2NT unavailable)#
|===

In the above auction, responder can set hearts as trump with a
splinter, so cannot ask for KC on this round.
The splinter could faked just to set trump for kickback.

=== Picture Jumps have priority over KC asking

Even after suit agreement, it may be necessary to delay asking for
key-cards.

