=== Four-level agreement

The general principle is that for 4m to be minorwood, we must first
explicitely agree the minor-suit, or set it as trumps
with a transfer after a notrump opening.

When 4m is the first call that shows support for partner's minor
then, except for the case below, it is not minorwood.

When a minor fit is first discovered at the 4-level, and the auction
is not defined as minorwood, then four of the cheapest unbid suit or
the fourth-suit is key-card asking.

If diamonds are agreed and clubs is the fourth or unbid suit,
then the cheaper of each player's [alert]#2nd-suit# is KC asking.

==== Unlimited hand raises a non-forcing-3m to 4m

When opener or responder bids a minor at the 3-level, a raise to 4m
is minorwood when: +
@ 3m bidder is limited
_ (we are not in a GF) +
@ there is no forcing bid below 4m
_ that agrees the minor +
@ the 4m bidder is unlimited

